      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The term \"fake news\" is now a highly weaponized rhetorical tool used by both sides of the political spectrum. While it certainly refers to demonstrably false information, it is frequently deployed by politicians to dismiss legitimate, critical journalism they disagree with. This tactic allows them to delegitimize opposing viewpoints without having to engage with the actual facts presented. Therefore, it functions as a broad smear against unfavorable reporting rather than solely as a descriptor of outright falsehoods.",
      "source": "target",
